# ── Build artefacts + dev tooling ──
# Vue admin source is dev-only — production assets ship pre-compiled
# in `assets/dist/` (committed). The `dev/` folder is too large to
# distribute and irrelevant to customer sites.
/dev/
/docs/
/node_modules/

# NOTE: `app/vendor/` is INTENTIONALLY committed — it's required at
# runtime (firebase-php, plugin-update-checker, etc.) and WordPress
# has no composer at install time, so a customer site cloned from
# git or unzipped from the release asset must boot without an extra
# `composer install` step. This matches the convention used by every
# major WP plugin (Yoast SEO, WooCommerce, BuddyPress, etc.).
# Composer dev-only deps stay excluded because we never `--require-dev`.

# Internal tooling / agent notes — must not ship to customer sites
# or appear in public GitHub repo.
CLAUDE.md
.gemini/
.claude/

# Build outputs from local zip helper
*.zip

# macOS finder cruft
.DS_Store

# IDE / editor
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*~
